values:
Rejoice, for there is a God and he has taken pity on me by giving me an actual good day! the first in a long line of bad days, tis the light at the end of the tunnel, only I am neither dead, nor in a cheesy episode of "Ghost Whisperer" where everytime the ghost-who-has-issues-comes-to-grips-with-death-and-makes-up-with-living-love-one-and-sees-the-light, and ofcourse has to ASK the ghost talking woman "what is that?" or "is that THE light?". This is one of those days, it was good becuase of various reasons which i will promptly list beginning...now!

1) In my Ancient History Class we finished "Kingdom of Heaven" , which we watched for our Medieval Europe section and I got the chance to once again bash Orlando Blooms "acting". Seriously, the guy was great till he opened his mouth and talked! he has the look! the action fighting, kicking butt skills! but the man it just aggrivatingly bad at acting! Even my teacher was making many jabs at him to me great glee, he said things that tickled me so, such as, "he cannot act his way out of a wet paper bag" and "I wish we could just put US out of HIS misary", and various other things that just made me guaf/laugh/snicker/choke on a gummiebear(which would be a perfectly fine way to die if i don't say so myself...death by artifically flavored gummie candy in the shape of a bear...yum). But yes, that was beginning of my fantastic day which moved onto...

2)me reading in a Scottish accent in my Liturature class, or atleast attempted. We were reading over a poem called "The Mouse" or "To the Mouse", i don't really remember, but i do remember my teacher tapping her chin and asking "who can do the scottish accent again?" (I did it earlier in the year with a sore throat so i slowly turned into a drunk Texan accent much to my friend's glee). And everyone, literally, everyone yelled "Nicole!" "Nykki!" or for those who don't know my name simply pointed at me and went "her!". Then my teacher smiled at me and was all "Ahhhhhh yes...Nicole, please read it in a Scottish accent for us". Now I did not mind, i mean, i love reading outloud, but this certain peice of work was infact a Bi*** to read, seriously...half the words I had no idea how to say. Once i stopped and asked the teacher how to pronouce the word and she just laughed saying "you are doing it better then I ever could"
So i finished, struggling to do the accent, which i only was able to do in a few parts since i was focused on trying to pronouce the words right. In the end the teacher said i was great and better then she could have ever done again, and she had that "I am sooooo making you do that again" smile. Later that day...

3) I met up with my best friend Ed for a span on 2 mintues and discussed me borrowing his "Chronclies of Narnia:LWW" DVD, a film that i love too much for my own good. We decided that i have to first give him back "Empire Records" and then he will give me Narnia...i agreed, the deal was struck, and on monday i get my Aslan and talking Beavers...woot!

So yes, all this made my day fun, may sound odd to some of you, but to my friends, it is understandable. OH and i got a Blizzard from DQ...Reesecup BLizzard baby! HUZZA!
Word yo!
I better go to bed since mummsie is telling me to get off and sleep.
as if i will sleep! i will read!
and then sleep...
becuase i am not a machine...

beep beep

ta!

Wow, it's me, and like always I don't really have anything wonderful to say other then um...high schools give too much homework over Spring Break, so much in fact that it literally made me stop in the middle of an essay and go "what the hell...it's Spring Break and I am here trying to explain why the Cold War happened! IT HAPPENED, pleeeaasseee get over it" and with that I proceeded to smash me head through the desk. But other then that I do have some good news, I have an audition next Sat. for a student film and an audition the next day for a Stage Play, so I am quiet pumped you know, almost hyped, but not quiet there.
On another note, we are about to delve into Pride & Prejudice in my Lit. class and all I can say is...
*drool*
Mr.DDDaaarrrrrccccyyyyy
*strange zombie like noise*
We won't be watching the film because we watched it in the beginning of the year (which is a bummer) but at least we get to read one of my favorite books, and we read it out loud during class, so I am going to attempt to steal the reading part of Elizabeth Bennett every class from Kathleen or Adrienne...it's MINE, hands of! Wha-cha!

So yeah, that is the master plan, I could always settle for Jane or Mrs. Bennett because she is such a barrel of fun, but I would rather Lizzy, just because I am like that. Speaking of Lit. I have worksheets to complete...but that can wait after I go on the journey to find the missing half of my writing assignment, meaning all of it. I had written 9 paragraphs and took them home to type them out, and now, they are in fact, missing! and I am in a fit of panic because they are late already because I went to a funeral, so I need to speak to my dear teacher and BEG him for an extension, I MAY cry real tears simply because I hate handing in late work...that reminds me...I have late religion homework.
DAMNIT ALL!
Why am I remembering all of this now the DAY before school?
Better yet why am I still sitting here?!!
Oh lordy I better go and attempt to finish it all.
Wish me luck wishbone
mama is gonna need it
